OL,7,FSheila says that once the rain starts
OL,8,Fthey begin to fear the inevitable.
OL,9,F"You just sit there and wait , we keep
OL,10,Fgoing to the drains, watching the
OL,11,Fdrains on the drive, making sure they
OL,12,Fdon't move."
OL,14,FStephen added: "It's a weird feeling
OL,15,Fbecause all the work you've done,
OL,16,Fwe've just had all the drives done,
OL,17,Fthe kitchen floor relaid, you know at
OL,18,Fthe back of your mind that you could
OL,19,Fbe minutes away from cutting it up."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/12
